<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-12-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-12-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-12-29"><hi rend="italic">December 29,
                                    1896</hi>.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Thirty-five naturalized Americans or the wives and children of such are
                            on ship from Harpoot to America. Nine revolutionists released from
                            Aleppo left Alexandretta last night on ship for Marseilles. Diradourian
                            leaves for America to-day on assurances from palace of security. Have
                            requested withdrawal of guard from Robert College.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>